	<section id="intro">  
		<h2 class="mb-4">Introduction</h2>
		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- About</h5>
			Kiwi is a premium adman dashboard template based on the latest version of bootstrap (4) framework
			<h5 class="my-4">- Terminology</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>When we use the word <strong>Layout</strong> we refer to the different structures of the template</li>
				<li><strong>layout directory</strong> or <strong>${layout}</strong> refers to for example: leftbar directory</li>
				<li>The word <strong>Assets</strong> refers to (css, images, js, etc..) files</li>
				<li><strong>Working Layout directory</strong> The ${layout} against which <strong>gulp tasks</strong> are executed</li>
			</ul>
			<h5 class="my-4">- Features</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>Built using the latest version of <a href="http://v4-alpha.getbootstrap.com/">bootstrap</a> (version 4.0.*)</li>
				<li>Well structured and organized files and code</li>
				<li>Uses <a href="http://sass-lang.com/">Sass</a> for preprocessing CSS</li>
				<li>Uses the powerful task management system<a href="http://gulpjs.com/">Gulp</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://bower.io/">Bower</a> and <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">NPM</a> for dependency management.</li>
				<li>We use <a href="http://assemble.io/">Assemble</a> for building HTML markup.</li>
				<li>Up till now Kiwi has 4 different layouts (basic, iconbar, leftbar and topbar)</li>
				<li>Light and Dark menubar themes</li>
				<li>Unlimited number of skins for the navbar</li>
				<li>Dozen of pre-built pages for common uses</li>
				<li>Hundreds of UI components (icons, widgets)</li>
				<li>Many useful javascript and css libraries for common tasks</li>
				<li>Responsive and mobile friendly structure</li>
				<li>All source and compiled files are included in the package</li>
				<li>We include our Gulp tasks for you to use in your development</li>
				<li>In the coming releases dozens of feature will be introduced</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

