	<section id="installation" class="mt-5">
		<h2 class="mb-4">Installation</h2>
		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- Zero Installation</h5>
			<p>We include all compiled files to be ready for use. if you don't need build tools, you don't have to install anything</p>
		</div>
		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4" id="build-section">- Using Build Tools</h5>
			<p>We use gulp for build processes. You can optionally use it, Compiled and ready files are included as mentioned above.</p>
			<p>You need node.js, npm and gulp installed on your machine in order to use our build utilities</p>
			<div class="alert alert-warning">
				Before installation you should set the gulp settings in <strong>config/gulp.js</strong> default setting will be used if you didn't.
			</div>
			<h5 class="my-4">- Configuration</h5>
			<p class="font-italic mb-4">
				All the following configuration options are in the <strong>config/gulp.js</strong>file
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><code>workingLayout</code>set this to one of the following layout names(leftbar, topbar)</li>
				<li class="text-danger">All gulp tasks that deal with the ${layout} do their work on the layout specified in <code>workingLayout</code></li>
				<li><code>srcDir</code>change this value if you changed the <strong>src</strong> directory name</li>
				<li><code>distDir</code>change this value if you want another name for the <strong>dist</strong> directory</li>
				<li><code>assetsDir</code>refers to <strong>src/assets</strong>directory</li>
				<li class="text-danger">all <strong>gulp tasks</strong>relies on those settings so be specific and don't change theme unless you have a good reason</li>
			</ul>
			<h4 class="my-4">- Installation</h4>
			<p>after configuration run the following commands</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					You should have <strong>Node</strong> and <strong>NPM</strong> installed on your machine in order to use the following commands
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>npm install gulp -g</code> installs <strong>gulp</strong> globally on the systems
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>npm install</code>run this command after navigating to the main directory of Kiwi
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp build</code> builds the <strong>dist</strong> folder form the <strong>src</strong> files
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>npm start</code>or <code>gulp serve:dist</code> to run a local server from the <strong>dist</strong> directory
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="commands" class="mt-5">
		<h2 class="mb-4">Gulp Commands</h2>
		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- SASS Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp sass</code>compiles <strong>.scss</strong> files from the working layout directory <strong>${layout}/scss</strong> to <strong>${layout}/css</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp sass:global</code>compiles <strong>.scss</strong> files from <strong>assets/global/scss</strong> to <strong>assets/global/css</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp sass:examples</code>compiles <strong>.scss</strong> files from <strong>assets/examples/scss</strong> to <strong>assets/examples/css</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp sass:vendor</code>compiles <strong>.scss </strong> files from <strong>assets/vendor/scss</strong> to <strong>assets/vendor/css</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp sass:all</code>runs all the above <strong>sass</strong> tasks i.e. <strong>(sass, sass:global, sass:examples, sass:vendor)</strong> at once.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- HTML Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp html</code>builds the <strong>HTML</strong> files form views to the working layout directory <strong>${layout}/</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp html:all</code>Assembles all layouts at once
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- Watch Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp watch:sass</code>watches <strong>.scss</strong> files in <strong>global, examples, vendor and ${layout}/scss</strong> directories and reloads the browser.
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp watch:scripts</code>watches <strong>.js</strong> files in <strong>global, examples, vendor and ${layout}/js</strong> directories and reloads the browser.
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp watch:html</code>watches <strong>.hbs(handlebars)</strong> files in <strong>views, templates, and ${layout}/templates</strong> directories and reloads the browser.
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp watch</code>runs all the above <strong>watch:*</strong> tasks at once
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- Copy Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp copy:bower</code>copies the main files from the <strong>/bower_components</strong> directory to <strong>src/assets/vendor</strong> directory
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- Clean Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:bower</code>removes the <strong>assets/vendor/bower_components</strong> directory
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:dist</code>removes the the dist directory
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:html</code>removes all <strong>${layout}/*.html</strong> files
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:html:all</code>removes <strong>*.html</strong> files from all layout directories i.e. (leftbar, topbar, basic and iconbar, etc..).
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:css</code>removes all <strong>${layout}/css/*.css</strong> files
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:css:global</code>removes all <strong>assets/global/css/*.css</strong> files
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:examples</code>removes all <strong>assets/examples/css/*.css</strong> files
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp clean:css:all</code>runs all <strong>clean:css, clean:css:global, clean:css:examples</strong>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-3 mb-4">
			<h5 class="mb-4">- Other Tasks</h5>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<code>gulp serve</code>runs the <strong>gulp watch</strong> task and runs a local server that serves the files in <strong>/src</strong>directory
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp serve:dist</code>serves the files in <strong>/dist</strong>directory
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp build</code>minifies files and copy assets and the working layout to the <strong>dist/</strong>folder
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>gulp build:all</code>minifies all assets and builds all layouts at once.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
